I was very disappointed with this cake. I did cut down on the sugars and oil by about 25%, however I found it very bland. I don't think upping those ingredients would have made a difference.

Rating: 4
This is a delicious cake. Like others I made a few modifications to the recipe. For the cake: 1) Instead of 1 cup of vegetable oil I used 1/2 cup of oil and 1/2 cup of plain yogurt. 2) I cut down the sugar from 2 cups to 1 1/4 cups. 3) I omitted the pineapple. For the frosting: 1) I omitted the cinnamon. 2) I added a few tablespoons of finely grated coconut and a tablespoon of milk. Preparation: Once cooled I cut the cake in half horizontally and used just under half of the frosting in the center of the cake. I put the other half of the frosting on the top. I added a few sprinklings of finely chopped pecans and a little grated carrot to the top for decoration. I made this cake for my husbands birthday and we enjoyed it with friends. Everyone complimented the look and taste of the cake. I will definitely make this one again.

