Rating: 3
I've made this twice and have been amazed just how good it turned out each time. The second time I left out the pineapple (I really didn't care for the texture of the pineapple). I increased the carrot and banana by half a cup each and substituted 1cup of apple sauce for 1 cup of oil; it exceded my expectations by far. I have to say that I also left out the cinnamon in the frosting as being English we don't go a bundle on it (the cinnamon in the cake is just perfect though). I have also frozen the cake for a later date and that worked really well too. I have been enjoying constant compliments for this cake; I'm glad that I could let you into my secret!

