Rating: 3
Great cake with interesting flavors--mainly a carrot cake, but the pineapple, banana and pecans add depth. I decreased the vegetable oil by 1/2 cup and added 1/2 c. applesauce as others suggested. I felt it could have used a bit more moisture--perhaps increasing oil by 2T. Also, I decreased amount of brown sugar by 1/4c. with great results. A wonderful frosting is the Orange Cream Cheese Frosting (10/99 issue). Also, I baked it in two 9" rounds (mine were perfectly done in 20 minutes). I will definitely make this one again.

Rating: 3
This is a great, easy recipe for cake or muffins. It is moister than a banana bread but less carrotty than a carrot cake. We didn't like the cinnamon cream cheese frosting, though - it is much better with orange cream cheese frosting. The kitchen smells marvelous while it is baking!

Rating: 2
I too made this as cupcakes (24; bake 25-30 min) and used the orange-cream-cheese frosting instead of the one in the recipe. I also used 2/3 c applesauce (actually peach mango sauce, come to think of it) and just 1/3 c oil in the cake. The batter tasted a little too sweet to me, so when I mashed the banana I mixed in the juice of one lemon, and that seemed to help. The final result was okay; moist, yes, but considerably more like a banana bread than a carrot cake. I might make these for a brunch, unfrosted, and call them muffins, but I will not make this again as a dessert. Still, they were decent.

