I love this cake. It is one of the staples in my recipe file. Since my family is weight conscious and we love our sweets, I use only one-third cup oil and substitute applesauce and/or plain yogurt for the other two-thirds. I often also use an egg substitute to further cut fat and calories. It always turns out rich and moist and keeps well.

